<p>Perplexity AI processes over 1.2 billion search queries per month. It grew 800% year over year. And Gartner predicts traditional search volume will drop 25% by 2026 because of AI chatbots like Perplexity (<a href="https://www.gartner.com/en/newsroom/press-releases/2024-02-19-gartner-predicts-search-engine-volume-will-drop-25-percent-by-2026-due-to-ai-chatbots-and-other-virtual-agents">Gartner</a>).</p>
<p>Perplexity SEO is no longer optional. It is a new acquisition channel. The platform has 45 million monthly active users who ask questions and get answers with cited sources. If your website is one of those cited sources, you get traffic without a single ad dollar.</p>
<p>The problem: most SEO teams still treat Perplexity like Google. They optimize for keywords, chase backlinks, and ignore the structural changes that AI search engines reward. The result is zero citations and zero referral traffic from a platform growing faster than any search engine in history.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries. Our content appears in AI search results across Perplexity, ChatGPT, and Google AI Overviews. The optimization process overlaps with traditional SEO in some areas. In others, it requires an entirely different approach.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn in this guide:</p>
<ul>
<li>What Perplexity SEO is and how it differs from Google SEO</li>
<li>How Perplexity selects which sources to cite</li>
<li>8 strategies to get your content cited by Perplexity</li>
<li>Technical setup for PerplexityBot crawler access</li>
<li>Common mistakes that block your content from AI citations</li>
<li>How to track and measure Perplexity referral traffic</li>
<li>A comparison of optimization tactics across Perplexity, ChatGPT, and Google AI Overviews</li>
</ul>
<h2>What Is Perplexity SEO</h2>
<p>Perplexity SEO is the practice of optimizing your website content to appear as a cited source in Perplexity AI search results. Unlike Google, where you rank as a blue link, Perplexity generates a written answer and displays source citations alongside it.</p>
<p>Getting "cited" by Perplexity means the platform references your page as evidence for a claim in its response. Each citation links back to your site. Users click these citations to verify information or learn more. That click is your traffic.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Perplexity SEO ranking factors and how citations work" src="/images/blog/perplexity-seo-ranking-factors.webp" /></p>
<p>This is a fundamental shift in how search works. Google shows 10 links and lets users choose. Perplexity reads dozens of pages, synthesizes an answer, and credits specific sources. Your goal is no longer to rank in position 1. Your goal is to be the source Perplexity trusts enough to cite.</p>
<p>The field falls under a broader discipline called <a href="/blog/generative-engine-optimization-guide/">generative engine optimization (GEO)</a>. GEO covers optimization for all AI search platforms. Perplexity SEO is GEO applied specifically to the Perplexity platform.</p>
