<h3>What Does Not Transfer</h3>
<p>These Google tactics have little or no effect on Perplexity citations:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Keyword density optimization.</strong> Perplexity understands semantics. Stuffing keywords hurts readability and citation chances.</li>
<li><strong>Backlink volume campaigns.</strong> Perplexity uses trust signals, but a page's link profile is not weighted like Google's PageRank.</li>
<li><strong>Long-tail keyword matching.</strong> Perplexity rephrases queries internally. Exact keyword matches matter less than covering the topic thoroughly.</li>
<li><strong>Ranking position.</strong> Being position 1 on Google does not guarantee a Perplexity citation. Perplexity re-evaluates independently.</li>
</ul>
