<h2>Common Perplexity SEO Mistakes</h2>
<p>These mistakes prevent content from earning Perplexity citations even when the content itself is good.</p>
<h3>Mistake 1: Burying the Answer</h3>
<p>Long introductions kill Perplexity citations. If your answer to the query starts at word 500, Perplexity has already found a cleaner source. Lead with the answer. Always.</p>
<h3>Mistake 2: Applying Google Keyword Tactics</h3>
<p>Keyword density, exact-match keyword placement in every H2, and synonym stuffing do not help with Perplexity. The AI understands semantics. Write clearly for the topic. Stop optimizing for keyword frequency.</p>
<h3>Mistake 3: Ignoring Content Freshness</h3>
<p>A post last updated in 2023 will not get cited in 2026. Perplexity date-checks aggressively. If your content does not have a recent publication or update date, it drops out of citation consideration.</p>
<h3>Mistake 4: Blocking PerplexityBot</h3>
<p>Many sites block unknown crawlers by default. If PerplexityBot cannot access your pages, no optimization strategy will help. Check your <code>robots.txt</code> and WAF settings before anything else.</p>
<h3>Mistake 5: Writing Walls of Text</h3>
<p>No headings, no lists, no tables, no structure. Perplexity struggles to extract useful passages from unstructured prose. Format your content for machine parsing.</p>
<h3>Mistake 6: No Named Author or Credentials</h3>
<p>Anonymous content with no author byline, no expertise signals, and no citations earns zero trust from Perplexity. Add author bios with relevant credentials. Cite your sources. Show your experience.</p>
<h3>Mistake 7: Targeting Queries Where Perplexity Does Not Cite</h3>
<p>Not every query triggers external citations. Perplexity sometimes answers from its training data alone, with no source links. Before optimizing for a query, search it on Perplexity and check if the response includes external citations. If it does not, that query is not a Perplexity SEO opportunity.</p>
<h2>How to Track and Measure Perplexity Citations</h2>
<p>You cannot improve what you do not measure. Here is how to track whether your Perplexity SEO efforts are working.</p>
