<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How does Perplexity AI choose which sources to cite?</strong></p>
<p>Perplexity searches the web, retrieves top-ranking pages, and runs a reranking model that scores each page for relevance, answer quality, freshness, and authority. It then generates an answer and attaches numbered citations to the highest-scoring sources. Direct answers in the first 100 words, recent publication dates, and structured content are the strongest signals.</p>
<p><strong>Is Perplexity SEO different from Google SEO?</strong></p>
<p>The foundation is the same: quality content, technical accessibility, and authority. The differences are in weighting. Perplexity values content freshness and direct answer placement much more than Google. Backlinks matter less. Content structure and extractability matter more. Think of Perplexity SEO as Google SEO plus additional formatting and freshness requirements.</p>
<p><strong>Does domain authority matter for Perplexity?</strong></p>
<p>Less than you think. Perplexity evaluates topical authority over global domain authority. A DR 25 niche site with 30 deep articles on one topic will outrank a DR 85 generalist site for that topic. Build depth in your niche rather than chasing domain-wide metrics.</p>
<p><strong>How do I check if Perplexity is citing my website?</strong></p>
<p>Search your target queries on perplexity.ai and look for your domain in the numbered citations. In Google Analytics 4, filter traffic by source containing "perplexity" to see referral volumes. For automated monitoring, tools like Otterly.AI and LLMClicks track citations across AI platforms.</p>
<p><strong>Can small websites get cited by Perplexity?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Small sites with deep topical expertise regularly earn citations over larger competitors. The keys are content freshness, direct answers, structured formatting, and demonstrable expertise. A 10-page site that covers one topic thoroughly can outperform a 10,000-page site that covers it superficially.</p>
<p><strong>What is the difference between Perplexity SEO and answer engine optimization (AEO)?</strong></p>
<p><a href="/glossary/answer-engine-optimization/">Answer engine optimization</a> is the broader category. It covers optimization for any platform that provides direct answers, including Google featured snippets, Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini. Perplexity SEO is AEO applied specifically to the Perplexity platform.</p>
<p>Perplexity SEO is where organic search is heading. The platform is growing faster than any search engine in the last decade, and every cited source gets direct referral traffic. Start with the BLUF method, structure your content for extraction, keep it fresh, and make sure PerplexityBot can access your pages. The brands that optimize for AI search now will own the citations that drive traffic for years.</p>
